Martyr Rajguru Chowk, Madam Cama Marg,
Mantralaya, Mumbai 400032

Preamble: My TST Mission 4.0 has announced the cash prizes to the winning local bodies in the 12 categories and the procedure for appropriation of the prize money vide Government Decision dated 27.09.2024 at Reference No. (1). Accordingly, a Detailed Project Report of the works to be taken up by the local bodies out of the award amount has been prepared vide Government Decision dated 08.02.2022 at Reference No. Administrative approval has to be obtained from a committee constituted under the chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change.

2. Accordingly, for grant of administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report received from the Awardee Local Bodies, Ms. The Committee has made recommendations after discussing the Detailed Project Report submitted by the Local Bodies in its meeting held on 02.05.2025 under the Chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment & Climate Change. It was under the consideration of the government to grant administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report of the respective local bodies as recommended by the committee.
The government's decision:

Considering the points mentioned in the Preamble, I would like to state that under Basundhara Abhiyan 4.0, the total amount received by Lohara Nagar Panchayat is Rs. The detailed project report of the works to be taken up out of the prize money of ₹1.75 crore, costing ₹1,75,22, 191.00 (₹one crore seventy five lakh twenty two thousand one hundred CHAOS only), has been submitted by the Lohara Nagar Panchayat with the technical approval of the City Engineer, Latur Municipal Corporation. As per the recommendation made by the said Committee, the total amount submitted by Lohara Nagar Panchayat is Rs. The works in the Detailed Project Report costing 1,75,22, 191.00 (Rupees one crore seventy five lakh twenty two thousand one hundred and ninety one only) are being approved by the Government Administration subject to the following conditions and conditions. The works for which administrative sanction is being granted are shown in the accompanying Annexure-9.
2. Terms and Conditions 1) The operational mechanism for the works in this Detailed Project Report shall remain in the Lohara Nagar Panchayat.

(2) A detailed project report of the implementation of the works mentioned in this Detailed Project Report and the physical progress report should be sent to my Vasundhara Mission Directorate by the 5th of every month.
3) The implementation of the works in this Detailed Project Report should be completed within the next 6 months from the approval of the Administrator.
4) If the amount of the prize exceeds the amount, it should be made out of self-funding.
5) In case of any increase in the original project cost in this Detailed Project Report for any reason, no additional funds / grants will be made available for the same.

3. Under Majhi Basundhara Abhiyan, Lohara Nagar Panchayat has been given a State level high jump of Rs.1.00 crore in the category of "Nagar Parishad B Nagar Panchayat Group (population less than 15 thousand)" and Rs.1.00 crore in the category of Chhatrapati Sambhaji Nagar Division. A total prize money of ₹1.75 crore has been received. Out of the prize money of Rs. The first instalment of ₹1 lakh has been disbursed to them. Since the detailed project report of the works to be taken out of this prize money has been granted administrative approval by the Government as per paragraph 1 above.

The remaining prize money of Lohara Nagar Panchayat is Rs. The Government is approving the disbursement of the second instalment of ₹1 lakh (₹AAEM lakh fifty thousand only) through the Maharashtra Pollution Control Board.
